eem to love Paddle: its G2 page has 4.5 out of 5 stars with over 150 reviews. Customers really like the fact that it’s easy to use, and that it’s a one-stop shop for everything a SaaS business needs.Who is Paddle best for?Paddle is best for businesses looking for an all-in-one solution for payment processing, or those who would prefer to work with a merchant of record, instead of managing pesky sales taxes themselves. If you’re interested in signing up for Paddle, you can do so via their website.Quaderno: A simple and scalable tax compliance solutionQuaderno is another powerful sales tax compliance solution that’s designed for SaaS and e-commerce businesses. It’s designed to handle complex tax scenarios, making it a great option for merchants with lots of international sales. Quaderno integrates with a wide variety of platforms, including PayPal, Braintree, Shopify, and Stripe.Core features The team at Quaderno knows that time is money, so they’ve designed Quaderno to have a suite of helpful features, such as:Automated tax calculations: Calculates sales tax, VAT, and GST based on customer location.Real-time tax reports: Provides insights into tax obligations across multiple jurisdictions.Economic nexus tracking: Monitors tax thresholds and alerts users when compliance action is needed.Automated invoicing: Generates tax-compliant invoices for every sale, ensuring international compliance.PricingQuaderno offers four tiers of pricing, with the Startup plan starting at $49 per month, the Business plan starting at $99 per month, and the Growth plan starting at $149/month. Additionally, Quaderno offers custom plans for large enterprise clients. Customer reviewsQuaderno is well liked by its customers, with the app receiving 4.7 out of 5 stars across more than 20 reviews on its G2 page. Customers seem to like how simple Quaderno makes the sales tax collection process.Who is Quaderno best for?Quaderno is great for companies with a lot of international business, as it’s designed to handle the complexities that come with collecting GST and VAT, in addition to the traditional sales taxes collected in the United States.If you’re interested in signing up for Quaderno, you can do so on their website.Wrapping things upUnfortunately, there isn’t a one-size-fits-all sales tax compliance solution, because no two companies have the exact same needs. Ultimately, the best sales tax automation software for you is going to depend on what features you’re looking for and which company or interface you’re most comfortable working with. However, it’s worth noting that Numeral’s easy-to-understand pricing and intuitive dashboard make it a great option for businesses that are looking for a simple sales tax automation solution.About the author
























