 using Numeral.PricingUnlike most of its competitors, Numeral has a straightforward pricing model, with a flat rate structure. Numeral charges $150 to register your business with a state, so you can begin collecting sales tax there. Then, once you’re registered with a state, Numeral charges $75 per filing, regardless of whether your company is doing $10,000 in revenue or $10,000,000 in revenue. Depending on usage, pricing for the sales tax API will vary.Customer reviewsCustomers love Numeral; its G2 rating is a whopping 4.9 out of 5 stars. Most of the reviewers rave about how much they love Numeral’s customer service team and how easy the app is to use.Who is Numeral best for?Numeral is great for people who are looking for sales tax automation software that’s easy to use and that has straightforward and easy-to-predict costs. When you’re working with Numeral, you have access to a team of experts to support you.If you’re interested in getting started with Numeral, you can book a demo or get started.Avalara: The most popular sales tax toolAvalara is a giant in the sales tax automation solution industry. Its client list includes some of the largest companies in the world. This means that Avalara has countless integrations with industry-leading accounting, e-commerce, and ERP systems, including QuickBooks, NetSuite, Salesforce, and Microsoft Dynamics. Core features Avalara is a preferred provider for large enterprise clients, because it has a wide variety of features to assist businesses operating at the highest level, such as:A comprehensive tax engine: Calculates accurate sales tax, VAT, and GST rates globally.Extensive filing and remittance options: Automates filing and payments in virtually any state or country, saving significant time for large-scale operations.Enterprise scalability: Handles large workloads and order volumes for large businesses.PricingUnfortunately, all of the bells and whistles that come with Avalara have a hefty price tag. Its pricing scheme isn’t publicly disclosed; however, Avalara users have posted online that Avalara costs high four-digit to low six-digit sums of money per year. This price puts it out of reach for many small and medium-sized businesses.Customer reviewsAvalara’s reviews are something of a mixed bag. It has 3.9 out of 5 stars on G2, out of nearly 600 reviews, with many reviewers complaining about its customer support and even issues with sales tax.Who is Avalara best for?Avalara was designed with the large enterprise in mind, so it probably won’t be a great fit for small or medium-sized businesses. However, companies with incredibly large transaction volumes might find Avalara worth its price.If you want to work with Avalara, you can book a demo to learn more. For a side-by-side comparison, check out our in-depth Avalara vs. Anrok comparison.TaxJar: A budget-friendly alternativeTaxJar is a very popular sales tax automation solution among small and midsize businesses. Its easy-to-understand subscription-based model is very cost-effective for businesses that have lower transaction volumes. TaxJar also integrates with a wide range of e-commerce, accounting, and ERP software, including BigCommerce, NetSuite, PayPal, and QuickBooks.Core featuresTaxJar is designed with the business owner in mind, offering a bunch of features that help streamline the sales tax process, including:Automated sales tax calculations: Ensures compliance with tax laws by calculating sales tax based on customer location.AutoFile: Saves business owners time by automatically filing sales tax returns where they have a tax obligation.Nexus tracking: Determines overall sales tax obligations by tracking where you have established nexus.PricingTaxJar has an easy-to-understand, tiered pricing structure that works for businesses with smaller order volumes. Their Starter plan starts at $19 per month, and their Professional plan starts at $99 per month. Both of these rates cover just 200 orders per month. If you receive more than 200 orders per month, then additional charges will apply.Customer reviewsCustomers seem to love TaxJar; it has 4.7 out of 5 stars on G2, with nearly 250 reviews. Their customers seem to love how easy it is to use, claiming that TaxJar allows them to put their sales tax obligations on “autopilot.” Who is TaxJar best for?TaxJar is a great option for smaller businesses, or businesses with smaller order volumes, that are looking for a straightforward solution to their sales tax woes. If you’re interested in signing up for TaxJar, you can do so right on their website — no demo required.For a side-by-side comparison, check out our in-depth TaxJar vs. Anrok comparison.Stripe Tax: A seamless option for Stripe usersAs you might guess, Stripe Tax is owned and operated by Stripe — one of the largest online payment processors in the world. This means that Stripe Tax integrates seamlessly with Stripe. In addition, Stripe Tax integrates with all of the platforms that Stripe integrates with. So, if you’re already a Stripe user, you might love Stripe Tax.Core features Stripe Tax has quite a few helpful tools and features to help make the lives of their users much easier, such as:Automated tax calculations: Automatically determines the correct sales tax, VAT, and GST based on customer location.Tax collection and reporting: Manages tax collection and generates reports to simplify compliance.Effortless implementation: Can be enabled with just a few clicks, so it’s easy to set up.Reduces manual effort: Automates tax management, minimizing the need for manual calculations.PricingSince Stripe Tax is part of the Stripe ecosystem, Stripe charges just an additional 0.5% fee on top of its processing fee. Although this is very straightforward, and there are no monthly fees to worry about, it can become costly for firms with large amounts of sales.Customer reviewsUnfortunately, there aren’t many reviews for Stripe Tax on its G2 page. However, the few reviews that are there are very positive,